Charmza Had it not been for the alertness and agility of Bafana Bafana keeper Ronwen Williams, South Africa would have suffered a defeat of massive proportions against their Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers opponents Morocco. The Bafana skipper played one of his most outstanding games to date despite the 2-1 defeat. It could have been more embarrassing, especially in the first half, but he kept the scoreline decent with his heroic performance. We rate Williams’s performance an eight out of 10.  For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.